_decoded_content.name: Wheelchair Cupholder
_decoded_content.description:
**Important Note:** _This model was originally designed to be printed on a Stratasys-style powder-bed printer. When printing with an FDM process it requires a lot of support. I've uploaded an improved design specifically for FDM printing which requires no support:_ http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:1204700

A cupholder I designed for my wife's wheelchair (a Quickie P222). It works well for normal cups and glasses as well as coffee mugs. The opening on the side makes it easy to insert and remove stemmed wine glasses. This version is designed to lock into a swing-away arm.

The model was designed using Fusion 360 and can be accessed here:
  • A360: http://a360.co/1Qq4SLg
  • Fusion 360 Gallery: https://gallery.autodesk.com/fusion-360/projects/wheelchair-cupholder
  • Attached STEP file: `cupholder_swing_away.stp`

The swing-away arm is for a Qtronix joystick. The part number is 882696 for right-hand or 882697 for left-hand. If you already have one, the swing-away assembly can be disassembled and reversed. Catalog link:

https://www.quickie-wheelchairs.com/wheelchair-parts/sunrise-medical/quickie-p222-se/electronics/qtronix-electronics/swing-away-round-arm-joystick-mount-qtronix

Bought new, these are rather expensive parts. Please comment with ideas for alternative mounting options.
